<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph>
[[ 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Puntius Hamilton</taxonomicName>
]]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="54">Discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="54">
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ater">Puntius ater</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="khugae">P. khugae</taxonomicName>
are unique among species of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Puntius</taxonomicName>
in Manipur in having one black longitudinal stripe on the side of the body. The former species is distinguished from the latter in having a black edge on the dorsal fin, 13-17 serrae (modally 13) on the dorsal fin spine, 10-11 (modally 10) predorsal scales, modally 26 or 27 (range = 25-29) lateral-line scales, and a longer gut (2.0-2.5 times total length). 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="khugae">Puntius khugae</taxonomicName>
has no black edge on the dorsal fin, 10-12 serrae (modally 10) on the dorsal fin spine, 9-10 (modally 9) predorsal scales, modally 29 (range = 28-30) lateral-line scales, and a shorter gut (0.9-1.2 times total length) (Tables 1 &amp; 3). Taki et al (1978) classified species of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Puntius</taxonomicName>
having broad and elevated infraorbital 3+4 in the 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="conchonius">Puntius conchonius-group</taxonomicName>
. The two new species have similar structures and thus may be included in the group.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="54">
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ater">Puntius ater</taxonomicName>
inhabits sluggish streams of the Imphal River and its tributaries, while 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="khugae">P. khugae</taxonomicName>
inhabits the Khuga, a comparatively faster clear-water stream. The latter species has a shorter gut (Fig. 2a &amp; b) and probably is a sympatric species adapted to a different environment with a different food habit.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="54">
Hamilton (1822) described 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ticto">P. ticto</taxonomicName>
from Gangetic basin. He observed the pelvic fin of the species to have one undivided ray in front and two behind. Similar observations were also made in the present study.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="54">
Hora et al. (1937) observed variations in 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ticto">P. ticto</taxonomicName>
and treated 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:024BBA69-1AD7-441A-AD9E-E0BC16D464BA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Puntius punctatus Day 1865:302" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctatus">P. punctatus</taxonomicName>
of Peninsular India and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:07E6EB40-ED0D-4732-9756-A6831809098D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Barbus Puntius stoliczkanus Day 1871:328" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stoliczkanus">P. stoliczkanus</taxonomicName>
of the Irrawady as its junior synonyms. Silas (1952), however, regarded 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:024BBA69-1AD7-441A-AD9E-E0BC16D464BA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Puntius punctatus Day 1865:302" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctatus">P. punctatus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:07E6EB40-ED0D-4732-9756-A6831809098D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Barbus Puntius stoliczkanus Day 1871:328" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stoliczkanus">P. stoliczkanus</taxonomicName>
as subspecies of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ticto">P. ticto</taxonomicName>
. Jayaram (1991) did not give subspecies status to 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:024BBA69-1AD7-441A-AD9E-E0BC16D464BA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Puntius punctatus Day 1865:302" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctatus">P. punctatus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stolizckanus">P. stolizckanus</taxonomicName>
as the fishes showed great variation in morphology. He also considered 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ticto">P. ticto</taxonomicName>
to be widely distributed and not restricted to any definite geographical region.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="54">
Day (1871) described 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:07E6EB40-ED0D-4732-9756-A6831809098D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Barbus Puntius stoliczkanus Day 1871:328" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stoliczkanus">P. stoliczkanus</taxonomicName>
from the Chindwin basin, Pegu and Moulmein. He reported the species to have a less compressed body and weaker serrations in the dorsal spine compared to 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ticto">P. ticto</taxonomicName>
. Hora (1936) distinguished 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:07E6EB40-ED0D-4732-9756-A6831809098D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Barbus Puntius stoliczkanus Day 1871:328" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stoliczkanus">P. stoliczkanus</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ticto">P. ticto</taxonomicName>
in having weaker serrations on the dorsal spine, and also in differences in the positions of lateral spots and the numbers of predorsal scales. Jayaram (1981) considered 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:07E6EB40-ED0D-4732-9756-A6831809098D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Barbus Puntius stoliczkanus Day 1871:328" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stoliczkanus">P. stoliczkanus</taxonomicName>
to be a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ticto">P. ticto</taxonomicName>
. Kottelat (2001) reported on the occurrence of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:07E6EB40-ED0D-4732-9756-A6831809098D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Barbus Puntius stoliczkanus Day 1871:328" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stoliczkanus">P. stoliczkanus</taxonomicName>
in the Irrawady, Salween, Mekong and Chao Phraya basins.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="54">
Early workers had access to very few, poorly preserved specimens. Thus, species were poorly described. Variations in ontogenic development were not considered, and several species from different geographically isolated habitats were put together as highly variable species. Various workers (Kottelat, 1996; Kottelat &amp; Lim, 1993, 1995; Ng &amp; Dodson, 1999; Ng &amp; Kottelat, 2000; Chakrabarty &amp; Ng, 2005; Ng, 2005) reexamined such ‘highly variable’ widely distributed species and concluded that they were in fact aggregates of distinct, often not even closely related species. 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ticto">Puntius ticto</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:07E6EB40-ED0D-4732-9756-A6831809098D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Barbus Puntius stoliczkanus Day 1871:328" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stoliczkanus">P. stoliczkanus</taxonomicName>
were also examined and found to be distinct (Table 1).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="55">
None of the fish collections from the Chindwin basins of the state contained 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="55" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ticto">P. ticto</taxonomicName>
. The species reported as 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="55" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ticto">P. ticto</taxonomicName>
by previous workers from the valley were probably misidentifications of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:07E6EB40-ED0D-4732-9756-A6831809098D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Barbus Puntius stoliczkanus Day 1871:328" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="55" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stoliczkanus">P. stoliczkanus</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="55" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ater">P. ater</taxonomicName>
. It may be concluded that 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="55" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ticto">P. ticto</taxonomicName>
is a Brahmaputra form, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:07E6EB40-ED0D-4732-9756-A6831809098D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Puntius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Barbus Puntius stoliczkanus Day 1871:328" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="55" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stoliczkanus">P. stoliczkanus</taxonomicName>
is a Chindwin form.
</paragraph>
